I've noticed that `isLocalLink` function fail to detect *local* in some cases.

https://github.com/excalidraw/excalidraw/blob/1bd416002ca9307f1dfc595e77b71713c8a811da/src/data/url.ts#L11-L13

For example, current `isLocalLink` will return `true` in following cases.

```js
// When current `origin` is https://excalidraw.com
isLocalLink("https://example.test/?url=https://excalidraw.com"); // => true
```

I not sure the definition of *local*, but presumably you want to determine whether it is a relative or absolute path.

If this is the case, a better implementation might be to check whether they are of the same origin.

```js
export const isLocalLink = (link: string | null) => {
  if (!link) {
    return false;
  }
  const current = new URL(location.href);
  const target = new URL(link, location.origin);
  return current.origin === target.origin;
};
```


